Xiao Wei, we need to go now.

198
00:14:10,610 --> 00:14:12,570
Wu Yan, you may leave now.

199
00:14:12,650 --> 00:14:14,760
It's been a long day. Go some rest.

200
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:16,220
Sure.

201
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:19,040
Xiao Wei, see you tomorrow.

202
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,860
See you tomorrow, Ms Sang.

203
00:14:20,940 --> 00:14:22,750
Get some rest.

204
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:56,480
It's Yi Jin's song.

205
00:14:58,060 --> 00:15:01,440
However, I really have the urge
to hug the person in front of me.

206
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:03,830
However, when he left quietly,

207
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:06,980
he made me think
that he has an odd temperament.

208
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:09,450
He doesn't usually express his thoughts,

209
00:15:09,530 --> 00:15:13,240
but he's always the gentle guy,
Su Nian Qin.

210
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,460
It's me.

211
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,290
I know.

212
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,540
You're right.

213
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:48,120
I'm too naive.

214
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:49,980
I...

215
00:15:50,060 --> 00:15:53,240
I can't take on the responsibility for
the consequences that Xiao Wei may face.

216
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:55,220
Just like today.

217
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,190
I thought it would be a cheerful event.

218
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:01,800
However, it turned out this way.

219
00:16:03,110 --> 00:16:04,590
Yet, I had no idea...

220
00:16:04,670 --> 00:16:08,020
what to do about it.

221
00:16:10,230 --> 00:16:11,360
When I was young,

222
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:13,640
I had to perform like this too.

223
00:16:15,060 --> 00:16:19,120
Those people sincerely think
that they're doing charity.

224
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,080
Of course,

225
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:23,120
I don't deny that.

226
00:16:24,890 --> 00:16:27,800
But they have no idea
what the kids really need.

227
00:16:29,110 --> 00:16:30,850
It's not that they have no idea.

228
00:16:32,410 --> 00:16:34,150
It's more like they didn't bother
to find out.

229
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:38,560
In front of the kids,
they repeatedly mention defects,

230
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:42,030
abandonment and orphans.

231
00:16:43,090 --> 00:16:46,000
They keep reminding the kids...

232
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,934
and keep making them think
that they're inferior to others.

233
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:51,680
However,

234
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:55,320
the disabled are merely those
with physical defects.

235
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:58,030
They're different from other people.

236
00:16:59,370 --> 00:17:01,199
We don't want to be sympathised.

237
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,660
We ask for equality.

238
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:07,590
Then...

239
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:10,390
Then, you...

240
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,669
It's okay. It's over now.

241
00:17:44,660 --> 00:17:45,560
Are you back yet?

242
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:48,460
You said you'd let me clean up
the interview draft tonight.

243
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:54,880
I'll give to you when I'm back.

244
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:04,500
